      "body" : "@jonasschnelli , @sdaftuar is right that that sync needs to be in there otherwise node 2 often doesn't even have its own 50BTC coin, because it has be reorged away by node 0's chain.  The sync ensures that node 0 builds off of node 2.  \r\n\r\nAs to why that causes failure, I haven't been paying attention to the changes introduced with fundrawtransaction, but I don't understand where your assumptions are coming from as to which coins should have been preferred.  It seems like several of the asserts fail.  `SelectCoinsMinConf` has a kind of messy randomized algorithm for selecting coins.",
